Hungary Plans 30% ’Accident Tax’ on Car Insurance, Origo Reports

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-10-14T06:06:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-14/hungary-plans-30-accident-tax-on-car-insurance-origo-reports.html
Hungary plans to levy a 30 percent
accident tax on obligatory third-party car insurance next year,
news portal  Origo  reported late yesterday, citing a draft
government document it obtained.  The tax will generate about 27 billion forints ($127
million) revenue next year for the state, Origo said, citing the
proposal which it said the Cabinet will present to parliament
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
